Name: Closure Element
Description: Make one number immune from cards for one turn.

Name: Distributive Element
Description: Select a number on the table and dublicate it into every player's set.

Name: Commutative Element
Description: Swap any two numbers on the table

Name: Pascal's Triangle
Description: Choose two adjacent numbers and replace them with their sum [recursive, you can perform as many times as you want.]

Name: Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic
Description: Replace the number with its prime decomposition set.

Name: Sheldon's Number
Description: The best number. Is this 73? Nah, check if 73 is in your set, if yes: use this as 73; if no: use this as 12.

Name: Googol
Description: Just 10 or search for a number on the table which is integer power of 10 and take one into your own set.

Name: The Answer
Description: What else do you think the meaning of the universe is?

Name: Lucky Number
Description: Roll the dice 2 times, if the sum is 7, add another 7 to the set.

Name: Fibonacci Number
Description: Every turn it is on the table without being used, it increases into the next Fibonacci number in the sequence. Starts from 1, stops once it's used or attacked.

Name: Graham's number
Description: It's too big, just replace it with 9.

Name: Cupid's Number
Description: Roll the dice twice. If and only if both dice are three or less, the constant is 29. Otherwise it is 14.
